p: Furthermore, we tested the SW for neutralizing Abs against influenza A/Luxembourg/43/2009 (H1N1/09) virus. Significant correlations were observed between H1N1/09 neutralizing titers with HA H1/09 IgG titer ( Fig 5B, Spearman r = 0.2538, p = 0.0002) as well as with HA stem-specific IgG titer ( Fig 5C, Spearman r = 0.1601, p = 0.0209). Whereas, IgG levels to HA of a pre-existing seasonal H1N1 virus, A/Texas/36/1991, showed no correlation with H1N1/09 neutralizing titers ( Fig 5D, Spearman r = 0.1128, p = 0.1066). These observations in SW indicate that pre-pandemic Ab levels to HA tri-stalk protein also translated into neutralizing activities against H1N1/09 virus.
